Num1= int(input('Give me a number'))
Num2 = int(input('Give me a number'))
total = Num1 + Num2

if (total%2 == 0):
    print('This value is even')
else:
    print("the value is odd")

    '''I created variables Num1 and Num2 and asked for the the users input. Their input gets stored and 
    converted into a integer. Then I created a variable called total which is the sum of the two numbers.
    I then I divided the total by two and used the remainder function to determine if it has a remainder. If 
    it does then it will print odd, if doesn't it will print even.'''